[[Category:Pages to sort]] [[Category:qq]]{{DEFAULTSORT:March 29 (Lunisolar)}}[[Category:qq]] [[cdo:3 nguŏk 29 hô̤ (nùng-lĭk)]] [[Category:Pages to sort]] [[Category:qq]]{{DEFAULTSORT:March 29 (Lunisolar)}}[[Category:qq]] [[zh-min-nan:3 goe̍h 29 ji̍t (kū-le̍k)]] [[Category:Pages to sort]] [[Category:qq]]{{DEFAULTSORT:March 29 (Lunisolar)}}[[Category:qq]] [[zh-yue:三月廿九]] {{Lunisolar March}} '''March 29''' is the 29th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. If the month is {{Nihongo|Small|小}} then this is the last day of the month. Otherwise if the month is {{Nihongo|Big|大}} then it is the second last day.<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20250111081847/https://www.chinaknowledge.de/History/Terms/calendar.html</ref><ref>https://www.nippon.com/en/japan-glances/jg00122/the-japanese-calendar.html</ref> Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Senshō|ja|先勝|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Chōkan|ja|長寛|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1163]] {{ill|May 4|ja|5月4日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The era name was changed from {{ill|Ōhō|ja|応保|12=draft|12=draft}} to {{ill|Chōkan|ja|長寛|12=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Kōan|ja|康安|12=draft|12=draft}} 1st year / {{ill|Shōhei|ja|正平|12=draft|12=draft}} 16th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1361]] {{ill|May 4|ja|5月4日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The Northern Court changed its era name from {{ill|Enbun|ja|延文|12=draft|12=draft}} to {{ill|Kōan|ja|康安|12=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Tenna|ja|天名|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1683]] {{ill|April 25|ja|4月25日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – "Yaoya Oshichi" was executed by immolation at Suzukamori Prison. * {{ill|Genroku|ja|元禄|12=draft|12=draft}} 9th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1696]] {{ill|April 30|ja|4月30日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – The Tokugawa shogunate permitted landfill of Edo city waste, which led to the creation of the island now known as {{ill|Eidaijima|ja|永代島|12=draft|12=draft}}. * {{ill|Xianfeng|ja|咸豊|ko|함풍|uk|Сяньфен|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1853]] {{ill|May 6|ja|5月6日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – During the Taiping Rebellion, Hong Xiuquan entered Nanjing, renaming it Tianjing and establishing it as the capital of the Taiping Heavenly Kingdom.
== Births == * [[Ōei]] 8th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1401]] {{ill|May 12|ja|5月12日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Shōkō Tennō|ja|称光天皇|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 101st Emperor of Japan (died [[1428]]). * {{ill|Hōreki|ja|宝暦|12=draft|12=draft}} 12nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1762]] {{ill|April 23|ja|4月23日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Iizuka Iga-shichi|ja|飯塚伊賀七|12=draft|12=draft}}, an inventor (died [[1836]]). * {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 11th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[1828]] {{ill|May 12|ja|5月12日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Hirano Kunomi|ja|平野国臣|12=draft|12=draft}}, a retainer of the Fukuoka Domain (died [[1864]]).
== Deaths == * [[Shitō]] 3rd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft}} [[997]] {{ill|May 8|ja|5月8日|12=draft|12=draft}}) – {{ill|Taizong of Song|ja|太宗|12=draft|12=draft}}, the 2nd Emperor of the Song dynasty (born [[939]]).
