* {{ill|Chōkan|ja|長寛|qq=|12=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft}} [[1163]] {{ill|May 4|ja|5月4日|qq=|12=draft}}) – The era name was changed from {{ill|Ōhō|ja|応保|qq=|12=draft}} to {{ill|Chōkan|ja|長寛|qq=|12=draft}}.
* {{ill|Kōan|ja|康安|qq=|12=draft}} 1st year / {{ill|Shōhei|ja|正平|qq=|12=draft}} 16th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|12=draft}} [[1361]] {{ill|May 4|ja|5月4日|qq=|12=draft}}) – The Northern Court changed its era name from {{ill|Enbun|ja|延文|qq=|12=draft}} to {{ill|Kōan|ja|康安|qq=|12=draft}}.
* {{ill|Tenna|ja|天名|qq=|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft}} [[1683]] {{ill|April 25|ja|4月25日|qq=|12=draft}}) – "Yaoya Oshichi" was executed by immolation at Suzukamori Prison.
* {{ill|Genroku|ja|元禄|qq=|12=draft}} 9th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft}} [[1696]] {{ill|April 30|ja|4月30日|qq=|12=draft}}) – The Tokugawa shogunate permitted landfill of Edo city waste, which led to the creation of the island now known as {{ill|Eidaijima|ja|永代島|qq=|12=draft}}.
* {{ill|Xianfeng|ja|咸豊|ko|함풍|uk|Сяньфен|qq=|12=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|12=draft}} [[1853]] {{ill|May 6|ja|5月6日|qq=|12=draft}}) – During the Taiping Rebellion, Hong Xiuquan entered Nanjing, renaming it Tianjing and establishing it as the capital of the Taiping Heavenly Kingdom.

