{{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=三月廿九|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 3월 29일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar March|qq=}} '''March 29''' is the 29th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. If the month is {{Nihongo|Small|小|qq=}} then this is the last day of the month. Otherwise if the month is {{Nihongo|Big|大|qq=}} then it is the second last day.<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20250111081847/https://www.chinaknowledge.de/History/Terms/calendar.html</ref><ref>https://www.nippon.com/en/japan-glances/jg00122/the-japanese-calendar.html</ref> Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} day is {{ill|Senshō|ja|先勝|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
== Events == * {{ill|Chōkan|ja|長寛|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} [[1163]] {{ill|May 4|ja|5月4日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) – The era name was changed from {{ill|Ōhō|ja|応保|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} to {{ill|Chōkan|ja|長寛|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. * {{ill|Kōan|ja|康安|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 1st year / {{ill|Shōhei|ja|正平|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 16th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} [[1361]] {{ill|May 4|ja|5月4日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) – The Northern Court changed its era name from {{ill|Enbun|ja|延文|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} to {{ill|Kōan|ja|康安|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. * {{ill|Tenna|ja|天名|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} [[1683]] {{ill|April 25|ja|4月25日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) – "Yaoya Oshichi" was executed by immolation at Suzukamori Prison. * {{ill|Genroku|ja|元禄|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 9th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} [[1696]] {{ill|April 30|ja|4月30日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) – The Tokugawa shogunate permitted landfill of Edo city waste, which led to the creation of the island now known as {{ill|Eidaijima|ja|永代島|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. * {{ill|Xianfeng|ja|咸豊|ko|함풍|uk|Сяньфен|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} [[1853]] {{ill|May 6|ja|5月6日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) – During the Taiping Rebellion, Hong Xiuquan entered Nanjing, renaming it Tianjing and establishing it as the capital of the Taiping Heavenly Kingdom.
== Births == * [[Ōei]] 8th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} [[1401]] {{ill|May 12|ja|5月12日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) – {{ill|Shōkō Tennō|ja|称光天皇|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, the 101st Emperor of Japan (died [[1428]]). * {{ill|Hōreki|ja|宝暦|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 12nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} [[1762]] {{ill|April 23|ja|4月23日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) – {{ill|Iizuka Iga-shichi|ja|飯塚伊賀七|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, an inventor (died [[1836]]). * {{ill|Bunsei|ja|文政|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} 11th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar|2=ja|3=グレゴリオ暦|4=fr|5=Calendrier grégorien|6=de|7=Gregorianischer Kalender|8=tl|9=Kalendaryong Gregoryano|10=ru|11=Григорианский календарь|ja|グレゴリオ暦|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} [[1828]] {{ill|May 12|ja|5月12日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) – {{ill|Hirano Kunomi|ja|平野国臣|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, a retainer of the Fukuoka Domain (died [[1864]]).
== Deaths == * [[Shitō]] 3rd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|ja|ユリウス暦|1=Julian calendar|2=ja|3=ユリウス暦|4=zh|5=儒略曆|6=ru|7=Юлианский_календарь|8=de|9=Julianischer_Kalender|10=es|11=Calendario juliano|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}} [[997]] {{ill|May 8|ja|5月8日|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) – {{ill|Taizong of Song|ja|太宗|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, the 2nd Emperor of the Song dynasty (born [[939]]).
