{{Not to be confused with|March 29|qq=March 29}}[[Category:Days of the Japanese Lunisolar Calendar]]<!--why is this category always showing up as 347 members?--> {{afc comment|1=This article as with the other date articles is relatively limited in scope to Japan. Reviewing the translation of this is good and also adding content translated from Chinese and Korean wikipedias will also be good. Both wikipedias are also relatively centered around their own countries for their Lunisolar calendar dates[[User:Immanuelle|Immanuelle]] ([[User talk:Immanuelle|talk]]) 00:16, 28 April 2025 (UTC)}} {{Globalize|article|Japan|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Chinese|1=三月廿九|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Expand Korean|1=음력 3월 29일|topic=hist|date=April 2025}} {{Lunisolar March|qq=}} '''March 29''' is the 29th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/March (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. If the month is {{Nihongo|Small|小|qq=}} then this is the last day of the month. Otherwise if the month is {{Nihongo|Big|大|qq=}} then it is the second last day.<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20250111081847/https://www.chinaknowledge.de/History/Terms/calendar.html</ref><ref>https://www.nippon.com/en/japan-glances/jg00122/the-japanese-calendar.html</ref> Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Senshō|ja|先勝|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senshō|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 六曜}}.
== Events == * [[:en:Chōkan|Chōkan]] 1st year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[:en:1163|1163]] [[:en:May 4|May 4]]) – The era name was changed from [[:en:Ōhō|Ōhō]] to [[:en:Chōkan|Chōkan]]. * [[:en:Kōan (Muromachi period)|Kōan]] 1st year / [[:en:Zhengping|Shōhei]] 16th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1361]] [[:en:May 4|May 4]]) – The Northern Court changed its era name from [[:en:Enbun|Enbun]] to [[:en:Kōan (Muromachi period)|Kōan]]. * {{ill|Tenna|ja|天名|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenna|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1683]] [[:en:April 25|April 25]]) – "Yaoya Oshichi" was executed by immolation at Suzukamori Prison. * [[:en:Genroku|Genroku]] 9th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1696]] [[:en:April 30|April 30]]) – The Tokugawa shogunate permitted landfill of Edo city waste, which led to the creation of the island now known as {{ill|Eidaijima|ja|永代島|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Eidaijima|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 永代橋}}. * {{ill|Xianfeng|ja|咸豊|ko|함풍|uk|Сяньфен|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Xianfeng|qq=}} 3rd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1853]] [[:en:May 6|May 6]]) – During the Taiping Rebellion, Hong Xiuquan entered Nanjing, renaming it Tianjing and establishing it as the capital of the Taiping Heavenly Kingdom.
== Births == * [[Ōei]] 8th year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[1401]] [[:en:May 12|May 12]]) – [[:en:Emperor Shōkō|Shōkō Tennō]], the 101st Emperor of Japan (died [[1428]]). * [[:en:Hōreki|Hōreki]] 12nd year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1762]] [[:en:April 23|April 23]]) – {{ill|Iizuka Iga-shichi|ja|飯塚伊賀七|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iizuka Iga-shichi|qq=}}, an inventor (died [[1836]]). * [[:en:Bunsei|Bunsei]] 11th year ([[:en:Gregorian calendar|Gregorian calendar]] [[1828]] [[:en:May 12|May 12]]) – {{ill|Hirano Kunomi|ja|平野国臣|qq=|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hirano Kunomi|qq=}}, a retainer of the Fukuoka Domain (died [[1864]]).
== Deaths == * [[Shitō]] 3rd year ([[:en:Julian calendar|Julian calendar]] [[997]] [[:en:May 8|May 8]]) – [[:en:Thái Tông|Taizong of Song]], the 2nd Emperor of the Song dynasty (born [[939]]).
