'''March 29''' is the 29th day of the month {{ill|March (Lunisolar)|ja|3月 (旧暦)|lt=March (Yayoi)|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/March (Lunisolar)|qq=}}, the 3rd month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|13=User:Immanuelle/Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|qq=}}. If the month is {{Nihongo|Small|小|qq=}} then this is the last day of the month. Otherwise if the month is {{Nihongo|Big|大|qq=}} then it is the second last day.<ref>https://web.archive.org/web/20250111081847/https://www.chinaknowledge.de/History/Terms/calendar.html</ref><ref>https://www.nippon.com/en/japan-glances/jg00122/the-japanese-calendar.html</ref> Its {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Rokuyō|qq=}} day is {{ill|Senshū|qid=Q96759839|1=senshū}}{{efn|ja|先勝|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q9418169}}{{efn|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Senshō|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 六曜|1=Rokuyō|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q9418169}}.

== Events ==
* {{ill|Chōkan|en|Chōkan|qid=Q1193904|lt=Chōkan|1=Chōkan}} 1st year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1163|en|1163|qid=Q19672|lt=1163|1=1163}} {{ill|May 4|en|May 4|qid=Q2549|lt=May 4|1=May 4}}) – The era name was changed from {{ill|Ōhō|en|Ōhō|qid=Q1193927|lt=Ōhō|1=Ōhō}} to {{ill|Chōkan|en|Chōkan|qid=Q1193904|lt=Chōkan|1=Chōkan}}.
* {{ill|Kōan (Muromachi period)|en|Kōan (Muromachi period)|qid=Q515424|lt=Kōan|1=Kōan (Muromachi period)}} 1st year / {{ill|Zhengping|en|Zhengping|qid=Q11123413|lt=Shōhei|1=Zhengping}} 16th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1361|en|1361|qid=Q6159|lt=1361|1=1361}} {{ill|May 4|en|May 4|qid=Q2549|lt=May 4|1=May 4}}) – The Northern Court changed its era name from {{ill|Enbun|en|Enbun|qid=Q1145071|lt=Enbun|1=Enbun}} to {{ill|Kōan (Muromachi period)|en|Kōan (Muromachi period)|qid=Q515424|lt=Kōan|1=Kōan (Muromachi period)}}.
* {{ill|Tenna|ja|天名|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tenna|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1683|en|1683|qid=Q7651|lt=1683|1=1683}} {{ill|April 25|en|April 25|qid=Q2531|lt=April 25|1=April 25}}) – "Yaoya Oshichi" was executed by immolation at Suzukamori Prison.
* {{ill|Genroku|en|Genroku|qid=Q1325001|lt=Genroku|1=Genroku}} 9th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1696|en|1696|qid=Q7699|lt=1696|1=1696}} {{ill|April 30|en|April 30|qid=Q2536|lt=April 30|1=April 30}}) – The Tokugawa shogunate permitted landfill of Edo city waste, which led to the creation of the island now known as {{ill|Eidaijima|ja|永代島|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Eidaijima|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 永代橋|1=Eitai Bridge|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11549876}}.
* {{ill|Xianfeng|ja|咸豊|ko|함풍|uk|Сяньфен|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Xianfeng|1=Xianfeng Era|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q1135843}} 3rd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1853|en|1853|qid=Q7666|lt=1853|1=1853}} {{ill|May 6|en|May 6|qid=Q2552|lt=May 6|1=May 6}}) – During the Taiping Rebellion, Hong Xiuquan entered Nanjing, renaming it Tianjing and establishing it as the capital of the Taiping Heavenly Kingdom.

== Births ==
* {{ill|Ōei|en|Ōei|qid=Q1193078|lt=Ōei|1=Ōei}} 8th year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|1401|en|1401|qid=Q6110|lt=1401|1=1401}} {{ill|May 12|en|May 12|qid=Q2559|lt=May 12|1=May 12}}) – {{ill|Emperor Shōkō|en|Emperor Shōkō|qid=Q451827|lt=Shōkō Tennō|1=Emperor Shōkō}}, the 101st Emperor of Japan (died {{ill|1428|en|1428|qid=Q6315|lt=1428|1=1428}}).
* {{ill|Hōreki|en|Hōreki|qid=Q1194397|lt=Hōreki|1=Hōreki}} 12nd year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1762|en|1762|qid=Q7652|lt=1762|1=1762}} {{ill|April 23|en|April 23|qid=Q2527|lt=April 23|1=April 23}}) – {{ill|Iizuka Iga-shichi|ja|飯塚伊賀七|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iizuka Iga-shichi|1=Igashichi Iizuka|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11666171}}, an inventor (died {{ill|1836|en|1836|qid=Q7601|lt=1836|1=1836}}).
* {{ill|Bunsei|en|Bunsei|qid=Q1327119|lt=Bunsei|1=Bunsei}} 11th year ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|en|Gregorian calendar|qid=Q12138|lt=Gregorian calendar|1=Gregorian calendar}} {{ill|1828|en|1828|qid=Q7570|lt=1828|1=1828}} {{ill|May 12|en|May 12|qid=Q2559|lt=May 12|1=May 12}}) – {{ill|Hirano Kunomi|ja|平野国臣|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Hirano Kunomi|1=Hirano Kuniomi|comment=changed title based on wikidata|qid=Q11483648}}, a retainer of the Fukuoka Domain (died {{ill|1864|en|1864|qid=Q7704|lt=1864|1=1864}}).

== Deaths ==
* [[Shitō]] 3rd year ({{ill|Julian calendar|en|Julian calendar|qid=Q11184|lt=Julian calendar|1=Julian calendar}} {{ill|997|en|997|qid=Q23571|lt=997|1=997}} {{ill|May 8|en|May 8|qid=Q2555|lt=May 8|1=May 8}}) – {{ill|Thái Tông|en|Thái Tông|qid=Q21406321|lt=Taizong of Song|1=Thái Tông}}, the 2nd Emperor of the Song dynasty (born {{ill|939|en|939|qid=Q23422|lt=939|1=939}}).

